The paper discusses dynamic zero-sum games, which are a subfield of game theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes the use of information relaxations, which are a common technique in machine learning and optimization, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper deals with optimization and control problems, which are often studied in the sub-categories cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), respectively, making them also likely sub-categories.
